olive oil
2 radish
1 cucumber
1 packet tahini
1 packet Garlic Dip
1 tomato
2 flatbreads
1 packet pulled chicken
1 packet roasted almonds
1 bag herbs
1 bag salad leaves
1 packet Balsamic & Olive Oil Dressing
1 sachet Middle Eastern Seasoning
½ sachet Turkish Sumac Seasoning

• Thinly slice celery and cucumber.
Roughly chop tomato
• In a small bowl, combine tahini and
garlic dip
• Toast or grill flatbreads to your liking

• Heat olive oil in a frying pan over
high heat. Cook chicken and Middle
Eastern seasoning until browned
and fragrant, 3-4 mins
• In a large bowl, combine salad
leaves, celery, cucumber, tomato,
chicken mixture and balsamic
dressing

• Slice flatbread into quarters
• Divide chicken salad between plates.
Top with almonds and torn herbs
• Sprinkle over sumac seasoning
(1/2 sachet for 2P / 1 sachet for 4P)
• Serve with flatbreads and
tahini-garlic dip.